        <div class="learning-experience">
            <h2 data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="1500">Technical Deep Dive</h2>
            <p data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="1500">Building Batrina was an advanced journey into complex app
                architecture and backend logic.
                Key technical milestones included:</p>
            <ul>
                <li data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="1500"><strong>Advanced State Management:</strong>
                    Utilizing <strong>Cubit & Provider</strong> to handle complex global states like Cart, User Profile,
                    and Themes.</li>

                <li data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="1500"><strong>Complex Business Logic:</strong>
                    Implementing a multi-dimensional inventory system (Matrix) where stock depends on both Color and
                    Size variants.</li>

                <li data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="1500"><strong>Firebase Transactions:</strong>
                    Ensuring data integrity during high-concurrency situations (e.g., two users buying the last item).
                </li>

                <li data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="1500"><strong>Deep Linking Architecture:</strong>
                    Configuring intent filters and handling incoming links for a frictionless "Click-to-Open"
                    experience.</li>

                <li data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="1500"><strong>Scalable Architecture:</strong>
                    Designing a codebase that supports immediate switching between User and Admin modes dynamically.
                </li>

                <li data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="1500"><strong>Performance Optimization:</strong>
                    Achieving 60 FPS through image caching, lazy loading, and efficient widget rebuilds.</li>
            </ul>
